{"questionId":"9066749","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Hemoglobin contains heme groups with the porphyrin ring bound to an iron(II) ion.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/776b5ab14944d8433466f1ab85ddac47145abcb5.png\" width=\"273\" height=\"313\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">A hemoglobin’s oxygen dissociation curve is shown.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/e97b4f76e873be265cea46a3d7f8f3e90a838dab.png\" width=\"521\" height=\"388\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Explain the shape of the curve.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">sigmoid/S-shaped<br><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br>as oxygen binds to one active site, shape of other active sites change&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">affinity of other sites for oxygen increases/ability to bind oxygen is increased by initial binding of oxygen<br><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br>cooperative binding &nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>Accept description of sigmoid/S-shaped curve if not stated for M1.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9066749","referenceCode":"19M.3.hl.TZ2.b(i)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Explain the shape of the curve.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","B: Biochemistry","B.9 Biological pigments (HL only)","Options","B: Biochemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}